{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-04-20T20:10:08.820478+00:00", "modified": "2026-04-22T17:20:21.378292+00:00", "id": 19671294, "conceptrecid": "19671293", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19671294", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.19671293", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19671294", "metadata": {"title": "Chemical composition ofleaves consumed by the lesser dog-faced fruit bat, Cynopterus brachyotis, in peninsular Malaysia", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19671294", "publication_date": "1999", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the Bat Literature Project) This study was designed to determine the chemical composition of leaves consumed by the lesser dog-faced fruit bat, Cynopterus brachyotis. Our results indicate that the mean protein content in leaves was 11.59%, whereas the mean calcium content was 7.21 mg/g dry mass. Mean tannins and phenols values were 4.13 and 8.01%, respectively. Levels of tannins and phenols were not correlated with concentrations of protein or calcium. Our results suggest that the chemical composition of leaves consumed by C. brachyotis is sufficient to meet daily protein and calcium requirements, especially during late pregnancy and lactation when energy and nutrient demands are expected to be the highest.", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Rajamani, Leela", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Aminah, Abdullah", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zubaid, Akbar", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tan, KIM Hoii", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kunz, Thomas H.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/c3cb8d5af88cdb3089c9ceffc843938a", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/504c9969125c6937828cac5df6b28957cae65dc9d7de2cecd73e6108aa09e97f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/DNMZ8C57", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "sc